# Laravel Deployment Guide (Ubuntu + Nginx + PHP-FPM + Let's Encrypt + systemd)

# Overview

This guide explains how to deploy a Laravel application on Ubuntu using:

* Nginx
* PHP-FPM
* Composer
* MySQL/PostgreSQL
* Let's Encrypt SSL
* Cloudflare (Optional)
* systemd (Queue Workers & Scheduler)

This guide assumes you are hosting multiple projects on the same server.

---

# Recommended Directory Structure

```
/home/ubuntu/Documents/projects/

├── CRM/
│   ├── app/
│   ├── bootstrap/
│   ├── config/
│   ├── database/
│   ├── public/
│   ├── resources/
│   ├── routes/
│   ├── storage/
│   ├── vendor/
│   └── .env
│
├── Inventory/
│   └── ...
│
└── ERP/
    └── ...
```

Each Laravel application should have its own:

* Project folder
* .env
* Database
* Nginx configuration
* Queue worker (optional)

---

# 1. Install Required Packages

Update Ubuntu

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

Install Nginx

```bash
sudo apt install nginx
```

Install PHP

Example (PHP 8.5)

```bash
sudo apt install php8.5-fpm \
php8.5-cli \
php8.5-mysql \
php8.5-pgsql \
php8.5-curl \
php8.5-mbstring \
php8.5-xml \
php8.5-bcmath \
php8.5-zip \
php8.5-gd \
php8.5-intl
```

Install Composer

```bash
sudo apt install composer
```

Verify versions

```bash
php -v
composer --version
nginx -v
```

---

# 2. Install Dependencies

Inside the project

```bash
cd /home/ubuntu/Documents/projects/CRM
```

Install packages

```bash
composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader
```

Copy environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Generate application key

```bash
php artisan key:generate
```

Configure database

```bash
nano .env
```

Run migrations

```bash
php artisan migrate
```

---

# 3. Set Permissions

Laravel requires write access to:

* storage
* bootstrap/cache

```bash
sudo chown -R ubuntu:www-data storage bootstrap/cache

sudo chmod -R 775 storage bootstrap/cache
```

---

# WARNING

If permissions are incorrect you may see

```
Permission denied
```

or

```
Unable to create cache
```

or

```
The stream or file could not be opened
```

---

# 4. Test Laravel

Run

```bash
php artisan serve
```

Visit

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

If Laravel does not work here

STOP

Fix Laravel before configuring Nginx.

---

# 5. Configure Nginx

Create

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/crm
```

HTTP

```nginx
server {

    listen 80;

    server_name crm.example.com;

    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;

}
```

HTTPS

```nginx
server {

    listen 443 ssl;
    http2 on;

    server_name crm.example.com;

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/example.com/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/example.com/privkey.pem;

    root /home/ubuntu/Documents/projects/CRM/public;

    index index.php index.html;

    location / {

        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;

    }

    location ~ \.php$ {

        include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;

        fastcgi_pass unix:/run/php/php8.5-fpm.sock;

    }

    location ~ /\.ht {

        deny all;

    }

}
```

Enable

```bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/crm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
```

---

# 6. Test Nginx

```bash
sudo nginx -t
```

Expected

```
syntax is ok

test is successful
```

Reload

```bash
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

---

# 7. Verify PHP-FPM

Check

```bash
sudo systemctl status php8.5-fpm
```

Expected

```
active (running)
```

Socket

```bash
ls -l /run/php/
```

Expected

```
php8.5-fpm.sock
```

---

# WARNING

If the socket does not exist

Check

```bash
sudo systemctl restart php8.5-fpm

sudo journalctl -u php8.5-fpm
```

