# 9. Install Certbot

```bash
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx
```

Generate certificate

```bash
sudo certbot --nginx -d crm.example.com
```

Multiple domains

```bash
sudo certbot --nginx \
-d blessed.co.zw \
-d crm.blessed.co.zw \
-d api.blessed.co.zw
```

---

# 10. Firewall

Ubuntu

```bash
sudo ufw allow OpenSSH

sudo ufw allow 80/tcp

sudo ufw allow 443/tcp
```

AWS Security Group

Allow

* 22
* 80
* 443

---

# 11. Queue Worker (Optional)

Create

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/crm-worker.service
```

Example

```ini
[Unit]
Description=CRM Laravel Queue Worker
After=network.target

[Service]
User=ubuntu
Group=www-data

WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu/Documents/projects/CRM

ExecStart=/usr/bin/php artisan queue:work

Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

Reload

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload

sudo systemctl enable crm-worker

sudo systemctl start crm-worker
```

---

# 12. Scheduler (Optional)

Edit cron

```bash
crontab -e
```

Add

```cron
* * * * * cd /home/ubuntu/Documents/projects/CRM && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1
```

